  "chapter": {
    "number": 1,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Judgment to Come"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is the word of the LORD that came to Micah the Moreshite in the days of Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judahâ€”what he saw regarding Samaria and Jerusalem:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hear, O peoples, all of you;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "listen, O earth, and everyone in it!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "May the Lord GOD bear witness against you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the Lord from His holy temple.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For behold, the LORD comes forth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "from His dwelling place;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He will come down and tread",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "on the high places of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The mountains will melt beneath Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the valleys will split apart,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "like wax before the fire,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like water rushing down a slope.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All this is for the transgression of Jacob",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the sins of the house of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "What is the transgression of Jacob?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Is it not Samaria?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "And what is the high place of Judah?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Is it not Jerusalem?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I will make Samaria",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "a heap of rubble in the open field,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "a planting area for a vineyard.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will pour her stones into the valley",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and expose her foundations.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All her carved images will be smashed to pieces;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "all her wages will be burned in the fire,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and I will destroy all her idols.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Since she collected the wages of a prostitute,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they will be used again on a prostitute.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Weeping and Mourning"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Because of this I will lament and wail;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "I will walk barefoot and naked.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I will howl like a jackal",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3805
          },
          {
            "text": "and mourn like an ostrich.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3806
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For her wound is incurable;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "it has reached even Judah;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "it has approached the gate of my people,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as far as Jerusalem itself.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do not tell it in Gath;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3807
          },
          {
            "text": "do not weep at all.",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Roll in the dust in Beth-leaphrah.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3808
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Depart in shameful nakedness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O dwellers of Shaphir.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3809
          },
          {
            "text": "The dwellers of Zaanan",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3810
          },
          {
            "text": "will not come out.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Beth-ezel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3811
          },
          {
            "text": "is in mourning;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "its support is taken from you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the dwellers of Maroth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3812
          },
          {
            "text": "pined for good,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but calamity came down from the LORD,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "even to the gate of Jerusalem.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Harness your chariot horses,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O dweller of Lachish.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3813
          },
          {
            "text": "You were the beginning of sin to the Daughter of Zion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for the transgressions of Israel were found in you.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore, send farewell gifts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3814
          },
          {
            "text": "to Moresheth-gath;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3815
          },
          {
            "text": "the houses of Achzib",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3816
          },
          {
            "text": "will prove deceptive",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "to the kings of Israel.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "I will again bring a conqueror against you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O dweller of Mareshah.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3817
          },
          {
            "text": "The glory of Israel will come to Adullam.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shave yourselves bald and cut off your hair",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in mourning for your precious children;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "make yourselves as bald as an eagle,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for they will go from you into exile.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
